text: Ayatollah Mohammad Feyz Sarabi (; 23 August 1928 – 11 April 2022) was an Iranian Shiite cleric and politician. He was a member of the 4th and 5thAssembly of Experts from the East Azerbaijan electorate from 2006 until his death. He was born in Sarab, East Azerbaijan, Iran. Feyz Sarabi died on 11 April 2022 in Qom, Iran at the age of 93.نماینده آذربایجان شرقی در مجلس خبرگان رهبری درگذشت ==References== Category:1928 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Iranian politicians
